                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File 25010/22.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Italian Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the fact that Charlton’s arrest, to secure which the preliminary
                    mandate described in article 2 of the convention of 1884 is issued, has, it is
                    reported, already been secured upon the complaint of the Italian consul, and in
                    view of your telegram of June 25, I assume that you are now awaiting
                    instructions from your Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
